{"_id":"61f6ede6-ef35-3e05-ac1f-58561306966c","authorName":"Stephen Cleary","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"ad2250182ff26a84dda974e50cd94382","message":"A \"continuation\" is just a task that is started automatically based on some condition. So, it doesn't make sense to \"attach\" an already-running task as a continuation.\r\n\r\nSince continuations are tasks, you can just have the ContinueWhenAll continuation do both things: aggregate the results and process the results.","postId":"2015_01_a-tour-of-task-part-7-continuations-de3f4e98-d7b9-38d9-b8a9-e608dcf2d0c1","replyTo":"9323c408-5fcb-3aec-86ab-8d3e91458508","date":"2016-01-06T12:06:00Z","timestamp":1452081960,"authorUserId":"disqus:stephen_cleary"}